acceptOwnership().details: The new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

initiateGatewayToL1MigrationOnGateway(ui.details: This function can be called multiple times on the Gateway as it does not have a direct effect.

initiateL1ToGatewayMigrationOnL2(bytes32.details: This function can be called multiple times on the chain it does not have a direct effect.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pendingOwner().details: Returns the address of the pending owner.

receiveMigrationOnL1((uint256,uint256,ui.details: It sends the corresponding L1->L2 messages to the L2 and the Gateway.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Starts the ownership transfer of the contract to a new account. Replaces the pending transfer if there is one. Can only be called by the current owner.

initiateGatewayToL1MigrationOnGateway(ui.notice: Migrates the token balance from Gateway to L1.

initiateL1ToGatewayMigrationOnL2(bytes32.notice: Migrates the token balance from L2 to L1.

processLogsAndMessages(((uint8,bool,uint.notice: note we don't process L1 txs here, since we can do that when accepting the tx.

receiveMigrationOnL1((uint256,uint256,ui.notice: This function receives the migration from the L2 or the Gateway.
